I want to contribute as a forum for this discussion so better decisions are made and freedom grows rather than being stifled by concentration of power. I‚Äôm hear to listen and learn more.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet:
One view is that regulations will better integrate Bitcoin in the financial system making on ramps simpler, speeding up adoption. 

The other view is government is inherently corrupt and incompetent and regulators will distort free markets and ultimately hold Bitcoin back.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet:
There are competing views on whether regulations are good or bad, and what regulations are appropriate. 

Open debate is consistent with the core values of Bitcoin and I encourage it.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Attempts to regulate this space are likely in the next Congress. We need to vote for candidates who understand and support the core values of Bitcoin. Lots of great efforts are happening in this arena, but there is lots of work to be done to ensure Bitcoin is apolitical.

tweet: Meanwhile, Huizar's trial date has officially been set for June 22, 2021. The @USAO_LosAngeles anticipates a grand jury will consider add'l charges against add'l defendants in a superseding indictment. Prosecutors will likely seek a unified trial date for all defendants.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Goldman is the fifth person to agree to plead guilty and cooperate with federal prosecutors. The others are former special aide to Huizar, George Esparza, political fundraiser Justin Kim, real estate consultant George Chiang, and former CM Mitch Englander. @SpecNews1SoCal

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Goldman has deep ties to City Hall. He served as acting Chief of Staff to two former City Council members, Hal Bernson (District 12) and Mike Hernandez (District 1), before transitioning to lobbying and consulting, mainly on issues of land use and real estate development.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Side note - when filing the report below for @SpecNews1SoCal I interviewed multiple sources who didn't want to be identified but claimed there were developers in LA who felt pressured by CM Huizar to hire lobbyist Morrie Goldman for an $11k/month retainer. https://t.co/pbSSdUbyzt

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Court filings also reveal that before September 2018, Company M contributed $50,000 to a PAC used to benefit Huizar‚Äôs political causes. In June 2018, Goldman secured a $25,000 contribution to the PAC for Richelle Huizar, plus a commitment for another $25,000 contribution.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: In his plea agreement, Goldman admits that in Sep 2018 he agreed w/ Huizar and a Company M executive that the developer would contribute $50,000 to a PAC established to support Huizar's wife's political campaign. In return, Huizar would vote against a union appeal of the project.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Goldman's firm repped SF-based developer Carmel Partners on 520 Mateo, a proposed high-rise in the Arts District (Project M). Feds say thanks to Huizar, the development was approved with minimal affordable housing units, despite being in an area desperate for low-income housing.

name: Natalie Brunell ‚ö°Ô∏è
tweet: Goldman (who is referred to as Lobbyist B in previous court filings) owns and operates the lobby firm Urban Solutions, LLC, which claims to specialize in negotiating and navigating City Hall approval for real estate projects, including hotels and high-rise apartment towers.
